originalText.text: The best place to dance tango in NYC. If I am in the city, this is where I will be on Fridays. I love the vibes and I really enjoy the level of dancing. Super friendly to beginners too. They also have a class for absolute beginners too. If you looking to take a class I highly recommend this event.

originalText.text: Very high level, many young people, nice location and music. Putting 3 stars only because of its unfriendliness. We were tourists from Italy, no interest, no curiosity to try new partners in dancing, and we dance for many years and are good dancers. Everyone is dancing only with the friends. Mirada here doesn't work.  If they can improve this social aspect, be more inclusive,  it will be 5 stars!

originalText.text: I love this cozy milonga! I am there nearly every Friday to teach! Join us if you are an absolute beginner 7-8pm :) (no experience or partner required!) After class 9pm-1am I love dancing with friends and enjoying yummy Ukrainian food. It feels like comfort food that your Ukrainian grandmother would cook for you. I love the combo plates, especially the sauerkraut pierogi. We are located at the back of the Ukrainian East Village Restaurant, so be sure to pop in and say hi if you're interested!
